                  <handDesc>                
                       <handNote script="Ethiopic" xml:id="h1" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/SinaiNewEt002#ms_i1">
                         <seg type="script">Pre-14th-century script.</seg>
                         <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                         <seg type="rubrication">Several lines (corresponding to the title) at the beginning of each epistle (e.g. <locus target="#77vb #111rb #120ra"/>), sometimes followed
                           by alternating black and red lines (e.g. <locus target="#52va #88ra #101vb"/>);
                           indications for readings in the upper margin and within the text; 
                           qʷǝm-sign and zǝya-sign; crux ansata with coronis; text dividers and elements of text dividers; numerals.</seg>
                         <desc>
                           The characters are somewhat irregularly written and spaced. 
                           The loops of <foreign xml:lang="gez">መ</foreign> are triangular and not separated; 
                           the upper dash of the vowel marker of <foreign xml:lang="gez">እ</foreign> is horizontal;
                           the vowel marker of <foreign xml:lang="gez">ስ</foreign> is composed of a vertical line and a horizontal line directed to the left;
                           the 7th order marker of <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሮ</foreign> is attached directly to the oblique line (e.g., <locus target="#27vb #59vb #130ra"/>); 
                           the shape of <foreign xml:lang="gez">ፈ</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="gez">ረ</foreign> is angular (e.g. <locus target="#22ra #58rb #107ra"/>);
                           the vowel marker of <foreign xml:lang="gez">ው</foreign> is attached to the upper part of the character (e.g. <locus target="#59ra"/>);
                           the loop is <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሎ</foreign> is attached to a stroke on the upper part of the character (e.g. <locus target="#22ra #58vb #107va"/>).
                           The qʷǝm-sign is written  embedded within
                           the text (e.g., <locus target="#5ra #25vb #59rb"/>) or 
                            rarely in the left margin of the column
                           (e.g., <locus target="#91vb"/>);
                           the zǝya-sign is written in the left margin of the column
                           (e.g., <locus target="#2rb #27ra #91vb"/>).
                           The word for God is always written as  two units (<foreign xml:lang="gez">እግዚአ፡ ብሔር፡</foreign>).
                           Numerals are written with dashes, only once without on <locus target="#28v"/>.</desc>
                     </handNote>
